<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <title>Analytics for ecommerce - ghostanalytics</title>
    <meta name="description" content="Cookieless analytics for ecommerce. Attribute orders to the campaigns and referrers that earned them, keep checkout free of a consent wall, and stay GDPR-safe for EU shoppers. Powered by ghostanalytics.">
    <meta name="theme-color" content="#0a0c0e">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Geist:wght@400;500;600;700;800&family=Geist+Mono:wght@400;500;600&display=swap">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/marketing.css">
  </head>
  <body>
    @include('site-nav')

    <main>
      <nav class="shell subnav" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span>
        <a href="/use-cases" data-no-router>Use cases</a><span class="sep">/</span>
        <span>Ecommerce</span>
      </nav>

      <section class="hero shell">
        <div>
          <p class="enter eyebrow">For ecommerce</p>
          <h1 class="d1 enter hero-title">Every order, tied to the click that earned it.</h1>
          <p class="d2 enter hero-sub">
            Track carts, checkouts, and revenue without a cookie banner slowing the sale. See which products, pages, and campaigns actually pay, with numbers that match your store.
          </p>
          <div class="d3 enter hero-actions">
            <a class="btn primary" href="/#install">Get your script tag</a>
            <a class="btn ghost" href="/dashboard">See a live dashboard</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <aside class="d2 enter panel" aria-label="Sample store revenue dashboard">
          <div class="panel-head">
            <span class="live">Revenue, last 30 days</span>
            <span class="panel-tag">Sample data</span>
          </div>
          <svg class="usecase-viz" viewBox="0 0 360 300" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet" role="img" aria-label="Store revenue of $65.7k over the last 30 days from 742 orders, trending up, with revenue split across organic search, paid social, and email" style="display:block;width:100%;height:auto;margin-top:1.1rem">
            <text x="4" y="14" fill="#6d777c" font-family="'Geist Mono',ui-monospace,monospace" font-size="11" letter-spacing="1.2">REVENUE · LAST 30 DAYS</text>
            <text x="4" y="48" fill="#eef2f3" font-family="'Geist',sans-serif" font-size="28" font-weight="700" letter-spacing="-0.5">$65.7k</text>
            <text x="4" y="66" font-family="'Geist Mono',monospace" font-size="10.5"><tspan fill="#46d3c0">▲ 18%</tspan><tspan fill="#9aa4a9"> vs last month · 742 orders</tspan></text>

            <path d="M8,186 L8,166 L46,158 L84,162 L122,138 L160,144 L198,120 L236,126 L274,102 L312,108 L344,88 L344,186 Z" fill="#46d3c0" fill-opacity="0.13"></path>
            <polyline points="8,166 46,158 84,162 122,138 160,144 198,120 236,126 274,102 312,108 344,88" fill="none" stroke="#46d3c0" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></polyline>
            <circle cx="344" cy="88" r="4.5" fill="#46d3c0"></circle>
            <line x1="8" y1="186" x2="352" y2="186" stroke="rgba(233,238,240,0.09)" stroke-width="1"></line>

            <text x="4" y="212" fill="#6d777c" font-family="'Geist Mono',monospace" font-size="10" letter-spacing="1">REVENUE BY CHANNEL</text>

            <text x="8" y="230" fill="#9aa4a9" font-family="'Geist Mono',monospace" font-size="9.5">Organic search</text>
            <text x="352" y="230" text-anchor="end" fill="#eef2f3" font-family="'Geist',sans-serif" font-size="10" font-weight="600">$28.4k</text>
            <rect x="8" y="234" width="344" height="8" rx="4" fill="rgba(233,238,240,0.07)"></rect>
            <rect x="8" y="234" width="344" height="8" rx="4" fill="#46d3c0" fill-opacity="0.92"></rect>

            <text x="8" y="256" fill="#9aa4a9" font-family="'Geist Mono',monospace" font-size="9.5">Paid social</text>
            <text x="352" y="256" text-anchor="end" fill="#eef2f3" font-family="'Geist',sans-serif" font-size="10" font-weight="600">$16.2k</text>
            <rect x="8" y="260" width="344" height="8" rx="4" fill="rgba(233,238,240,0.07)"></rect>
            <rect x="8" y="260" width="196" height="8" rx="4" fill="#46d3c0" fill-opacity="0.58"></rect>

            <text x="8" y="282" fill="#9aa4a9" font-family="'Geist Mono',monospace" font-size="9.5">Email</text>
            <text x="352" y="282" text-anchor="end" fill="#eef2f3" font-family="'Geist',sans-serif" font-size="10" font-weight="600">$12.5k</text>
            <rect x="8" y="286" width="344" height="8" rx="4" fill="rgba(233,238,240,0.07)"></rect>
            <rect x="8" y="286" width="151" height="8" rx="4" fill="#46d3c0" fill-opacity="0.4"></rect>
          </svg>
        </aside>
      </section>

      <section class="reveal section shell" aria-label="No consent wall in checkout">
        <div class="split">
          <div class="split-text">
            <h3>No consent wall between a shopper and the buy button.</h3>
            <p>
              A cookie prompt on the storefront costs you the first tap and a slice of every sale behind it. ghostanalytics stores nothing on the shopper, so there is no banner to dismiss and nothing standing between a visitor and checkout.
            </p>
            <ul class="mini-list">
              <li><span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>GDPR, CCPA, and PECR friendly, so EU shoppers see no popup.</li>
              <li><span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>Under 2 KB and first-party, so product pages stay fast.</li>
              <li><span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>Nothing written to the device, so nothing to opt out of.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <aside class="panel" aria-label="Sample orders by landing page">
            <div class="panel-head">
              <span class="live">Orders by landing page</span>
              <span class="panel-tag">Sample data</span>
            </div>
            <div class="top-pages" style="margin-top:1.1rem;">
              <div class="top-row"><span class="path">/products/tote</span><span class="bar"><span style="width:100%"></span></span><span class="count">228</span></div>
              <div class="top-row"><span class="path">/collections/new</span><span class="bar"><span style="width:64%"></span></span><span class="count">146</span></div>
              <div class="top-row"><span class="path">/products/mug</span><span class="bar"><span style="width:44%"></span></span><span class="count">101</span></div>
              <div class="top-row"><span class="path">/sale</span><span class="bar"><span style="width:31%"></span></span><span class="count">71</span></div>
            </div>
          </aside>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="reveal section shell" aria-label="Revenue attribution">
        <div class="rev split">
          <div class="split-text">
            <h3>Attribution that matches your revenue, not a sample.</h3>
            <p>
              GA thresholds and samples your reports right when a campaign gets interesting. ghostanalytics counts every order and carries the UTM tags through to the purchase, so you can tell the channel that drives traffic from the one that drives sales.
            </p>
            <ul class="mini-list">
              <li><span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>UTM source, medium, and campaign on every order.</li>
              <li><span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>Referrers sorted into search, social, and direct automatically.</li>
              <li><span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>One-click GA import, so last year's peak season moves with you.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <aside class="panel" aria-label="Sample revenue by source">
            <div class="panel-head">
              <span class="live">Revenue by source</span>
              <span class="panel-tag">Sample data</span>
            </div>
            <div class="top-pages" style="margin-top:1.1rem;">
              <div class="top-row"><span class="path" style="font-family:var(--sans);">Organic search</span><span class="bar"><span style="width:100%"></span></span><span class="count">$28.4k</span></div>
              <div class="top-row"><span class="path" style="font-family:var(--sans);">Paid social</span><span class="bar"><span style="width:57%"></span></span><span class="count">$16.2k</span></div>
              <div class="top-row"><span class="path" style="font-family:var(--sans);">Email</span><span class="bar"><span style="width:44%"></span></span><span class="count">$12.5k</span></div>
              <div class="top-row"><span class="path" style="font-family:var(--sans);">Direct</span><span class="bar"><span style="width:30%"></span></span><span class="count">$8.6k</span></div>
            </div>
          </aside>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="reveal section shell" aria-labelledby="ecom-track">
        <div class="section-head">
          <h2 id="ecom-track" class="section-title">What stores track.</h2>
          <p class="section-intro">The moments that decide a sale, each one a single function call from your storefront.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="qa-grid">
          <div class="qa"><h4>Add to cart</h4><p>Measure intent per product, so you see which items pull shoppers in before they buy.</p></div>
          <div class="qa"><h4>Checkout started</h4><p>Catch the drop-off between cart and payment, and spot the page that leaks orders.</p></div>
          <div class="qa"><h4>Purchase</h4><p>Your headline conversion, attributed back to the exact source, campaign, and landing page.</p></div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="reveal section shell-narrow" aria-labelledby="ecom-code">
        <div class="section-head">
          <h2 id="ecom-code" class="section-title">A sale is one line.</h2>
          <p class="section-intro">No SDK and no init call. Fire the order from your thank-you page with the value and any properties you want to break it down by later.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-grid">
          <div class="code">
            <div class="code-bar"><span>checkout.ts</span><span>JavaScript</span></div>
            <pre><span class="cmt">// on the order confirmation page</span>
<span class="tok">ghost</span>('purchase', { value: 68.00, currency: 'USD', items: 2 })

<span class="cmt">// or a lighter signal earlier in the flow</span>
<span class="tok">ghost</span>('add_to_cart', { product: 'tote', value: 34.00 })</pre>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="code-note">The <code>ghost()</code> function ships with the tracking script, so there is nothing extra to import. Properties like <code>value</code> become breakdowns in your dashboard, and the beacon <code>POST</code>s to your own <code>/collect</code> endpoint, so even ad-blockers count the sale.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="reveal section shell" aria-label="Get started">
        <div class="cta-band">
          <h2>Grow revenue, not your consent overhead.</h2>
          <div class="cta-actions">
            <a class="btn primary" href="/#install">Get your script tag</a>
            <a class="btn ghost" href="/use-cases" data-no-router>All use cases</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>

    @include('site-footer')
  </body>
</html>
